Yerry Mina will be heading back to Merseyside earlier than hoped after Colombia were eliminated from the Copa America at the quarter-final stage, According to Toffeeweb.com. The Everton centre-half scored an impressive penalty – complete with bizarre celebration where he removed his shin pads to reveal a couple of personal photographs – in the shootout after the match against Chile had finished 0-0 but William Tesillo missed his kick and Alexis Sanchez decisive penalty. Mina’s tournament is over despite not having conceded a goal during this year’s Copa.